Package: gnome-doc-utils
Version: 0.8.0
Revision: 2
Depends: <<
	glib2-shlibs (>= 2.12.0-1),
	libgettext3-shlibs,
	libiconv,
	libxml2-bin (>= 2.6.12-1),
	libxml2-py24 (>= 2.6.12-1),
	libxml2-shlibs (>= 2.6.12-1),
	libxslt-bin (>= 1.1.8-1),
	libxslt-shlibs (>= 1.1.8-1),
	python24,
	scrollkeeper
<<
BuildDepends: <<
	autoconf (>= 2.60-1),
	automake1.9,
	gettext-bin,
	gettext-tools,
	glib2-dev (>= 2.12.0-1),
	intltool,
	libgettext3-dev,
	libiconv-dev,
	libxml2 (>= 2.6.12-1),
	libxslt (>= 1.1.8-1),
	pkgconfig
<<
Replaces: yelp (<< 2.10.0-1)
Source: mirror:gnome:sources/%n/0.8/%n-%v.tar.bz2
Source-MD5: 50726331fef362dc94921f366fcc8ed2
ConfigureParams: --mandir=%p/share/man --disable-scrollkeeper --disable-dependency-tracking
CompileScript: <<
	env ACLOCAL="aclocal -I ." autoreconf -fvi
	PYTHON=%p/bin/python2.4 ./configure %c
	make
<<
InstallScript: make install DESTDIR=%d
DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING* ChangeLog po/ChangeLog:ChangeLog.po xml2po/ChangeLog:ChangeLog.xml2po NEWS README xml2po/TODO:TODO.xml2po
PostInstScript: <<
	if [ configure = "$1" ]; then
		scrollkeeper-update -q
	fi
<<
PostRmScript: <<  
	if [ remove != "$1" ]; then
		scrollkeeper-update -q
	fi
<<
Description: Tools and templates for Gnome documentation
DescDetail: <<
	gnome-doc-utils is a collection of documentation utilities for the
	Gnome project. Notably, it contains utilities for building
	documentation and all auxiliary files in your source tree, and it
	contains the DocBook XSLT stylesheets that were once distributed
	with Yelp.
<<
DescPort: <<
	Update to autoconf 2.60 so that all @ templates in .pc get replaced.
	See: http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=342327

	Need to help autoconf find g-d-u.m4 in the local source directory.
	See: http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=355521
<<
